WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:03.536
- ♪ Crashing through
the crowded halls ♪

00:03.602 --> 00:04.938
♪ Dodging girls
like ping pong balls ♪

00:05.004 --> 00:06.705
♪ Just to reach
the bathroom on time ♪

00:06.773 --> 00:08.475
♪ Hey! Hey! Hey!
Leaping over laundry piles ♪

00:08.541 --> 00:09.876
♪ Diapers you can
smell for miles ♪

00:09.943 --> 00:13.680
♪ Guy's gotta do
what he can to survive ♪

00:13.747 --> 00:16.216
♪ In the Loud House,
in the Loud House ♪

00:16.282 --> 00:17.650
♪ Duck, dodge,
push and shove ♪

00:17.717 --> 00:19.285
♪ It's how
we show our love ♪

00:19.352 --> 00:21.621
♪ In the Loud House,
in the Loud House ♪

00:21.688 --> 00:23.223
♪ One boy and ten girls ♪

00:23.289 --> 00:25.091
♪ Wouldn't trade it
for the world ♪

00:25.158 --> 00:28.128
♪ Loud! House! Loud! ♪

00:28.194 --> 00:30.830
{\an8}♪ Loud House! ♪♪
- Poo-poo!

00:34.634 --> 00:42.842
- ♪

00:42.909 --> 00:44.878
- MAN ON TV:
Welcome back to "Arggh!"

00:44.944 --> 00:46.746
I'm Hunter Specter

00:46.813 --> 00:49.482
and we're in a haunted salon
in Erie, Pennsylvania,

00:49.549 --> 00:52.619
tracking the ghost
of Armando, the Hairdresser.

00:52.685 --> 00:54.320
- [door thuds]

00:54.387 --> 00:56.089
- Wait a minute,
I'm picking up something

00:56.156 --> 00:58.057
on my "Arggh!"
ghost detector.

00:58.124 --> 00:59.893
- [device clicks]
- [chair swivels]

00:59.959 --> 01:01.261
- HUNTER: [gasps]
There he is!

01:01.327 --> 01:03.496
Now to trap him in my ghost
containment device.

01:03.563 --> 01:05.498
- [dramatic music]

01:07.801 --> 01:10.437
- Ugh! Does anyone
sweep this floor?

01:10.503 --> 01:11.538
- [loud whoosh]

01:11.604 --> 01:13.173
- [objects clattering]

01:13.239 --> 01:14.808
- HUNTER:
He's on the run!

01:14.874 --> 01:16.576
I'm gonna have
to improvise.

01:16.643 --> 01:20.447
- ♪

01:20.513 --> 01:23.349
- Back! Back,
poncy hairdresser!

01:23.416 --> 01:25.885
- [wind gusting]

01:25.952 --> 01:27.187
- Got him...

01:27.253 --> 01:30.056
by a hair, ha, ha!

01:30.123 --> 01:32.692
- That was amazing!
- I know!

01:32.759 --> 01:33.927
- I thought
he was a goner.

01:33.993 --> 01:35.428
- When that chair
spun around,

01:35.495 --> 01:36.463
I pee'd a little.

01:36.529 --> 01:37.997
I'm gonna write
my weekly fan letter

01:38.064 --> 01:40.333
to Hunter right now,
while I'm still excited.

01:40.400 --> 01:42.068
- HUNTER: Don't forget
to tune in next week

01:42.135 --> 01:43.470
for more of "Arggh!"'s

01:43.536 --> 01:46.706
tour of the 25 most haunted
places in America.

01:46.773 --> 01:49.375
We'll be visiting a spooky
groundskeeper's house

01:49.442 --> 01:52.645
at a cemetery in
Royal Woods, Michigan.

01:52.712 --> 01:55.715
{\an8}- CLYDE &amp; LINCOLN: Did he just
say Royal Woods, Michigan?

01:55.782 --> 01:57.484
- Now I pee'd a little.

01:58.985 --> 02:00.553
{\an8}This is it, Clyde.

02:00.620 --> 02:02.822
{\an8}Are you ready to watch
Hunter Specter in action?

02:02.889 --> 02:04.390
{\an8}- I was born ready, Lincoln.

02:04.457 --> 02:06.326
{\an8}Well, actually, I was
born a month early,

02:06.392 --> 02:08.360
{\an8}so, I wasn't ready
for much of anything.

02:09.795 --> 02:13.166
- Whoa, who knew there were
this many "Arggh!" fans.

02:13.233 --> 02:17.103
This is unacceptable.
We can't even see Hunter.

02:17.170 --> 02:18.605
- Don't worry, buddy.

02:18.671 --> 02:21.341
I've got my trusty "Arggh!"
ghost-seeking periscope.

02:22.742 --> 02:23.877
- What do you see?

02:23.943 --> 02:25.211
- Some kind of cave...

02:25.278 --> 02:28.581
with a lot of stalactites
and waxy-looking boulders.

02:28.648 --> 02:30.016
- MAN:
[snarling]

02:30.083 --> 02:31.551
- CLYDE &amp; LINCOLN:
[nervous laughter]

02:31.618 --> 02:33.620
- Come on, Clyde,
I have a better idea.

02:33.686 --> 02:34.954
- BOTH:
[zooming]

02:35.021 --> 02:36.990
- Okay, "Arggh!" cadets,
this is it.

02:37.056 --> 02:38.191
I'm going in.

02:38.258 --> 02:40.093
But don't worry,
you'll be able to watch

02:40.159 --> 02:42.428
all the paranormal action
on this screen.

02:42.495 --> 02:45.298
So, until we meet
again, cadets.

02:45.365 --> 02:46.332
- [door thuds, slams]

02:46.399 --> 02:49.869
- CROWD:
[cheering, hooting]

02:49.936 --> 02:51.170
- Sweet! Right, Clyde?

02:51.237 --> 02:52.939
We have a great view
of the screen.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.274
- Totally.

02:54.340 --> 02:56.543
It almost makes me
forget about my fear of heights.

02:56.609 --> 02:57.777
Almost.

02:57.844 --> 02:59.412
- BOTH:
[thud]

02:59.479 --> 03:03.116
- Ah! I've landed on my official
"Arggh!" ghost handcuffs.

03:03.182 --> 03:05.151
- Hey, you two.
No lying down on the job.

03:05.218 --> 03:06.452
Set your walkies
to channel 4

03:06.519 --> 03:07.954
and get your butts
in that house.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.589
We're about to
start shooting.

03:09.656 --> 03:11.925
- No, ma'am, we don't
work for "Arggh!"--

03:11.991 --> 03:13.293
- 'Cause you know
what they say--

03:13.359 --> 03:14.494
when you do what you love,

03:14.561 --> 03:16.296
you never work
a day in your life.

03:16.362 --> 03:19.899
Heh. Heh. Come on, Clyde,
we'd better get to our posts.

03:19.966 --> 03:21.334
- That's more like it.

03:21.401 --> 03:28.241
- ♪

03:28.308 --> 03:29.309
- [nose honking]

03:29.375 --> 03:30.476
- [garbage can thuds]

03:30.543 --> 03:32.278
{\an8}- Lincoln,
did you see that?

03:32.345 --> 03:34.180
{\an8}I've gotta get that tissue
for my scrapbook.

03:34.247 --> 03:35.915
{\an8}- Okay.
I'll cover for you.

03:35.982 --> 03:37.483
{\an8}- I want that tissue,
Lincoln.

03:37.550 --> 03:39.652
- ♪

03:39.719 --> 03:41.688
- Hey, what are you
two doofuses doin'?

03:41.754 --> 03:44.791
Get over to your position
and do not miss your cue.

03:44.857 --> 03:46.159
Quiet on the set!

03:46.225 --> 03:47.627
And action!

03:47.694 --> 03:48.661
- [clears throat]

03:48.728 --> 03:50.129
On this special
episode of "Arggh!",

03:50.196 --> 03:52.098
we're going to be
hunting for the ghost

03:52.165 --> 03:54.133
of Groundskeeper Jim.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.536
Locals say you can still
hear him some nights

03:56.603 --> 04:00.073
dragging his shovel
around the empty house.

04:00.139 --> 04:02.241
Hello? Hello?

04:02.308 --> 04:05.044
Are you here now,
Groundskeeper Jim?

04:05.111 --> 04:06.512
- [switch clicking on/off]

04:06.579 --> 04:08.648
- It's a sign!
He's in the house!

04:08.715 --> 04:09.682
- CROWD:
[gasps]

04:09.749 --> 04:11.517
- Hey, man, quit playing
with the lights.

04:11.584 --> 04:13.586
Hunter's trying
to catch a ghost.

04:13.653 --> 04:15.388
- Shhhh!

04:15.455 --> 04:19.257
- This will help me keep track
of the ghost's exact location.

04:20.760 --> 04:24.030
- [small rock clatters]
- [gasps] He's right there!

04:24.097 --> 04:27.033
Aha! got you cornered,
Groundskeeper Jim.

04:27.100 --> 04:28.868
- [device beeping]

04:28.935 --> 04:30.570
- Fire the gelatin!

04:32.271 --> 04:33.806
Fire! Fire!

04:33.873 --> 04:34.941
- [gelatin splooshing]

04:35.008 --> 04:38.177
- Ah, ectoplasm!

04:38.244 --> 04:40.546
- CROWD: [gasping, cheering]
- It's attacking me!

04:40.613 --> 04:43.583
Ah! This ghost
is shockingly strong!

04:43.650 --> 04:45.284
Ah! Take this!

04:45.351 --> 04:48.521
- [air whooshing]

04:48.588 --> 04:49.389
- Got him!

04:49.455 --> 04:52.191
Sorry, Jim,
you're grounded.

04:52.258 --> 04:55.061
- CROWD:
[cheering, hooting]

04:55.128 --> 04:57.463
- What was that?
I can't hear anything.

04:57.530 --> 04:59.298
- [light switch clicks on]
- [fans turns off]

04:59.365 --> 05:00.700
- And cut!
Great job, everyone.

05:00.767 --> 05:02.368
- Nice work with
the gelatin, guys.

05:02.435 --> 05:04.170
I didn't think you'd
hit me in the face,

05:04.237 --> 05:05.371
but I went with it.

05:05.438 --> 05:06.873
{\an8}Made the scene
even more believable.

05:06.939 --> 05:08.608
{\an8}[laughing]
- BOTH: [gasping]

05:08.675 --> 05:11.077
- I can't believe
Hunter's a fake.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.445
Think about all the time
we've wasted

05:12.512 --> 05:14.580
watching five seasons
of "Arggh!"

05:14.647 --> 05:17.216
I could have learned
to play the banjo.

05:17.283 --> 05:20.820
Clyde, you're kind
of quiet back there.

05:20.887 --> 05:23.122
- Lincoln, I just don't wanna
talk about it right now.

05:23.189 --> 05:24.624
- I get that, buddy.

05:26.459 --> 05:29.462
Delete, delete, delete,
delete, delete.

05:29.529 --> 05:30.596
De-lete.

05:30.663 --> 05:32.398
- What are you doing,
big brother?

05:32.465 --> 05:35.601
- I'm getting rid of all my
recorded episodes of "Arggh!"

05:35.668 --> 05:37.003
- Ooh, goody!

05:37.070 --> 05:39.539
More room for my show about
plastic surgeries gone wrong.

05:39.605 --> 05:41.207
- MAN's VOICE: Lincoln.
Come in, Lincoln.

05:41.274 --> 05:43.376
- Clyde, you sound old.

05:43.443 --> 05:45.945
- Ha, this is Clyde's dad.
Can you come over?

05:46.012 --> 05:48.748
Clyde is having an episode,
and I was specifically asked

05:48.815 --> 05:51.050
not to call Dr. Lopez
on her vacation.

05:51.117 --> 05:52.618
- I'll be right there.

05:53.853 --> 05:56.255
- He's been throwing out
his favorite possessions.

05:56.322 --> 05:58.391
He said something about
them all being fake.

05:58.458 --> 06:00.226
At least I think
that's what he said.

06:00.293 --> 06:01.961
It was hard to hear
over Howard's crying.

06:02.028 --> 06:03.930
- Well, can you blame me?
It's not just his things.

06:03.996 --> 06:06.499
He said he doesn't believe
in birthday wishes,

06:06.566 --> 06:08.301
magicians,
or leprechauns anymore--

06:08.367 --> 06:10.970
all the things that make
our little guy so special.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.106
[sobbing]

06:13.172 --> 06:15.308
- Wait, I think I know
what's going on.

06:15.374 --> 06:18.644
{\an8}Clyde, look, I know you're
upset about Hunter, but--

06:18.711 --> 06:19.946
- I'm not upset,
I'm grateful.

06:20.012 --> 06:22.381
He opened my eyes
to what a chump I've been.

06:22.448 --> 06:23.583
I mean, if he's a fake,

06:23.649 --> 06:25.585
everything else must
be fake, too.

06:25.651 --> 06:27.754
- [plates clanking]
- HOWARD: [sobbing]

06:27.820 --> 06:31.124
- Your "Operation Dessert
Storm" commemorative plates?

06:31.190 --> 06:32.992
{\an8}- Pssst! That show's
gotta be rigged.

06:33.059 --> 06:34.260
{\an8}No one could
really caramelize

06:34.327 --> 06:36.796
{\an8}100 crème brûlées
in five minutes.

06:36.863 --> 06:40.399
{\an8}- Our anti-alien
abduction helmets?

06:40.466 --> 06:42.535
{\an8}- [laughing]
Aliens.

06:42.602 --> 06:43.703
{\an8}There's no such thing.

06:43.770 --> 06:45.304
- Clyde, you don't
have to give up on

06:45.371 --> 06:47.106
everything you've
ever believed in.

06:47.173 --> 06:48.875
- Oh, but I do,
Lincoln. I do.

06:48.941 --> 06:50.076
- [object crashes]

06:50.143 --> 06:51.911
- Clyde, that was
your clock-radio.

06:51.978 --> 06:53.446
- Ah.

06:54.647 --> 06:57.116
- It's worse than I thought,
and I know who's to blame.

06:57.183 --> 06:58.384
- Where are you going?

06:58.451 --> 07:00.953
- To see a man
about a ghost.

07:02.388 --> 07:05.158
Hunter Specter--
if that's really your name.

07:05.224 --> 07:09.295
- [sighs] I already told
you guys payday is Wednesday.

07:09.362 --> 07:11.497
- I'm not on your crew.
I'm a fan.

07:11.564 --> 07:15.067
Well, I was until I saw what
really happens on your show.

07:15.134 --> 07:16.469
- Oh.

07:16.536 --> 07:19.005
- I can handle it, but my
friend Clyde is crushed.

07:19.071 --> 07:20.439
He was your biggest fan.

07:20.506 --> 07:22.275
He wrote you a letter
every week.

07:22.341 --> 07:23.543
- Wait, that Clyde?

07:23.609 --> 07:24.710
He's the only
fan who noticed

07:24.777 --> 07:27.380
when I switched to
an all-cotton jumpsuit.

07:27.446 --> 07:29.015
Oh, I feel terrible.

07:29.081 --> 07:31.584
I didn't get into this
business to trick kids.

07:31.651 --> 07:33.386
I wanted to hunt ghosts.

07:33.452 --> 07:34.821
- Then why don't you?

07:34.887 --> 07:35.988
- Oh, it's TV.

07:36.055 --> 07:37.356
We have a schedule,

07:37.423 --> 07:40.560
and if we can't find ghosts,
we have to fake it.

07:40.626 --> 07:41.894
- Yeah? Well,
now Clyde thinks

07:41.961 --> 07:44.063
everything he
ever loved is fake.

07:44.130 --> 07:46.999
- I wish I could undo that,
but I don't know how.

07:47.066 --> 07:49.235
We all know there's
not a real ghost here.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.537
- [bell dings]
- Or is there?

07:51.604 --> 07:53.873
- HOWARD: Now, Clyde,
you'll have to wait

07:53.940 --> 07:55.842
an hour after eating
to go swimming.

07:55.908 --> 07:56.709
You'll get cramps.

07:56.776 --> 07:57.977
- That's just a myth, Dad.

07:58.044 --> 08:00.580
{\an8}I suppose next you'll tell
me if I make this face,

08:00.646 --> 08:02.448
{\an8}it could freeze that way.

08:02.515 --> 08:03.916
What a load.

08:03.983 --> 08:05.985
- [gasps] That's it!
I'm calling Dr. Lopez.

08:06.052 --> 08:07.253
[sobbing]

08:07.320 --> 08:08.621
- Howard, no.
She needs this vacation.

08:08.688 --> 08:10.723
She and Robin
are trying to make it work.

08:10.790 --> 08:12.391
- [phone rings]
- Hey, Lincoln. What's up?

08:12.458 --> 08:15.094
- LINCOLN: Clyde, tune your
walkie to channel 4.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.362
You've gotta hear this.

08:16.429 --> 08:18.097
- [water splashes]

08:18.164 --> 08:19.398
- HUNTER:
Come in, all crew!

08:19.465 --> 08:20.933
Return to Royal Woods,
immediately.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.101
I have a real ghost here,

08:22.168 --> 08:24.370
but I can't catch him
without my equipment.

08:24.437 --> 08:26.572
- So? Just more of
Hunter's lies.

08:26.639 --> 08:29.642
- LINCOLN: But, Clyde,
the Royal Woods episode is over.

08:29.709 --> 08:30.776
Why would he be lying?

08:30.843 --> 08:32.812
- HUNTER:
All crew, do you copy?

08:32.879 --> 08:34.513
{\an8}- LINCOLN: Clyde,
we've got the equipment.

08:34.580 --> 08:36.448
{\an8}We can help him.
- Meh.

08:36.515 --> 08:37.750
{\an8}- LINCOLN:
Aw, come on.

08:37.817 --> 08:38.683
{\an8}- Meh!

08:38.751 --> 08:40.219
{\an8}- LINCOLN:
Do it for me, then?

08:40.285 --> 08:41.854
{\an8}- Hmmm...I guess.

08:44.524 --> 08:47.093
- [owl hooting]

08:47.159 --> 08:48.594
- Hello?

08:48.661 --> 08:52.098
- Ah, my faithful crew guys.
Thanks for coming back.

08:52.164 --> 08:53.432
There's a real
ghost in here.

08:53.499 --> 08:54.734
- We're not your crew guys,

08:54.800 --> 08:57.436
and why should we believe
anything you say?

08:57.503 --> 08:59.672
- 'Cause my cherry
soda just disappeared

08:59.739 --> 09:04.610
and everyone knows Groundskeeper
Jim loved cherry soda.

09:04.677 --> 09:07.580
- Wow, you're really
going for it.

09:07.647 --> 09:10.449
- [thunder crashes]
- [door slams]

09:10.516 --> 09:12.652
- Uh, that seemed
pretty real.

09:12.718 --> 09:14.287
- [object scraping]

09:14.353 --> 09:16.055
- [gasps]
Groundskeeper Jim's shovel!

09:16.122 --> 09:17.256
- Uh-huh.

09:17.323 --> 09:19.091
- [can thuds]
- CLYDE: Oh!

09:19.158 --> 09:20.660
Ch-ch-ch-cherry?

09:20.726 --> 09:21.994
It is him!
- [can clatters]

09:22.061 --> 09:23.829
- [objects clattering]
- [ghostly laughter]

09:23.896 --> 09:25.631
- CLYDE:
And he's on the run!

09:25.698 --> 09:27.500
- What do you say, guys?
Should we catch him?

09:27.566 --> 09:30.169
- [lively rock music]

09:30.236 --> 09:31.437
- [ghostly laughter]

09:31.504 --> 09:32.571
- He's over there!

09:32.638 --> 09:34.407
- [ghostly laughter
continues]

09:34.473 --> 09:35.841
- [door slams]

09:35.908 --> 09:37.476
- I got this!

09:37.543 --> 09:38.911
Ya-a-a-a-a!

09:38.978 --> 09:40.079
[thuds]

09:40.146 --> 09:41.213
A little help?

09:42.448 --> 09:43.382
- [door thuds]

09:43.449 --> 09:46.552
- [wardrobe rattling]

09:46.619 --> 09:47.853
- He's in there.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.655
- [quietly]
Follow my lead.

09:49.722 --> 09:51.924
- BOTH:
[zooming]

09:51.991 --> 09:53.259
- Now!

09:53.326 --> 09:55.227
- [lively rock music]

09:57.697 --> 09:59.999
- LINCOLN &amp; CLYDE:
[screaming]

10:00.066 --> 10:02.301
- It's working!

10:02.368 --> 10:04.837
- HUNTER: Ha, ha!
- ALL: We got him!

10:04.904 --> 10:06.639
- Yeah!
- Incredible!

10:06.706 --> 10:08.274
That was amazing,
Hunter!

10:08.341 --> 10:12.311
I'm going home to write you
another fan letter right now.

10:12.378 --> 10:14.747
{\an8}I believe! I believe!

10:14.814 --> 10:18.017
- I feel bad lying to Clyde,
but I'm glad he believes again.

10:19.752 --> 10:21.854
- This paint can shaker
really did the trick.

10:21.921 --> 10:24.957
- And the fishing line
on the door was perfect.

10:25.024 --> 10:26.625
- And that spring behind
the picture frame

10:26.692 --> 10:28.094
worked like a charm.

10:28.160 --> 10:30.796
- And that was a nice touch
with the flying soda can.

10:30.863 --> 10:32.398
I didn't know you
were gonna do that.

10:32.465 --> 10:33.399
- Yes, I--

10:33.466 --> 10:35.167
Wait, I thought
you did that.

10:35.234 --> 10:36.902
- No.

10:36.969 --> 10:40.606
- [ghostly belch]
- BOTH: [gasp]

10:40.673 --> 10:42.541
- HUNTER:
Hey, "Arggh!" cadets,

10:42.608 --> 10:45.344
we're here at a haunted
tugboat in Milwaukee,

10:45.411 --> 10:46.912
where locals say

10:46.979 --> 10:48.647
some nights you
can see the ghost

10:48.714 --> 10:50.216
of Captain Jack
swabbing the deck.

10:50.282 --> 10:52.651
I can't guarantee we'll
find him here tonight,

10:52.718 --> 10:55.388
but if we do,
he's mine!

10:55.454 --> 10:58.391
- Hey, guys, got you
a little snack.

10:58.457 --> 10:59.825
- Served on Clyde's

10:59.892 --> 11:01.727
"Operation Dessert Storm"
commemorative plates.

11:01.794 --> 11:02.995
- Thanks, Dads.

11:03.062 --> 11:04.930
But we're going swimming
right after this show,

11:04.997 --> 11:06.632
so, we should probably
wait an hour.

11:06.699 --> 11:08.000
- BOTH:
No worries!

11:09.568 --> 11:11.404
[excited squealing]
- Yay!

11:11.470 --> 11:13.539
- Oh, our son is back!

11:13.606 --> 11:16.275
- Howie, don't make
that face--

11:16.342 --> 11:17.877
it'll freeze that way.

11:22.181 --> 11:31.757
- ♪

11:31.824 --> 11:33.492
- [snoring loudly]

11:33.559 --> 11:35.127
- [boot thuds]
- [groans]

11:35.194 --> 11:37.163
What? Who is that?

11:37.229 --> 11:39.265
[sniffing]
Oh, Lana.

11:39.331 --> 11:41.300
Let me guess.
Another bad dream?

11:41.367 --> 11:44.537
- [snoring loudly]

11:44.603 --> 11:45.905
- [heavy thud]
- Lori!

11:45.971 --> 11:48.541
Can you get my tangles out?
- [bird chirps]

11:51.577 --> 11:54.180
- Ow!
Not like a gorilla!

11:54.246 --> 11:55.414
- [musical ring tone]

11:55.481 --> 11:57.216
- Sis will call you back,
Boo-Boo Bear.

11:57.283 --> 11:59.318
- Lola!
- [musical ring tone]

11:59.385 --> 12:00.386
- LORI:
[grunting]

12:00.453 --> 12:02.855
Hi, Boo-Boo Bear.
Sorry about that.

12:02.922 --> 12:06.058
- Lori, does this outfit
clash with my toenail color?

12:06.125 --> 12:07.359
- It's fine.

12:07.426 --> 12:09.361
So, Bobby,
how was your night?

12:09.428 --> 12:11.230
- BOTH: [grunting]
- Let go of me!

12:11.297 --> 12:12.598
- Oh, my beloved--
- Let go of me!

12:12.665 --> 12:15.067
- Guys, what are
you doing?

12:15.134 --> 12:16.335
- Luan broke Edwin's fang.

12:16.402 --> 12:18.204
Tell her she has to pay
for his dental work.

12:18.270 --> 12:19.405
- He's a statue!

12:19.472 --> 12:21.107
The only thing
I'm paying for

12:21.173 --> 12:22.475
is you getting
your brain checked.

12:22.541 --> 12:23.676
- If you give
me ten minutes,

12:23.742 --> 12:25.811
I can warm up
my MRI machine.

12:25.878 --> 12:28.781
- Or we could just
give her a CAT scan.

12:28.848 --> 12:30.416
[laughing]
Get it?

12:30.483 --> 12:31.951
- LORI:
Everybody, out!

12:32.017 --> 12:34.787
I'm trying to talk
to Bobby.

12:34.854 --> 12:36.422
[heavy sigh]
Finally.

12:36.489 --> 12:38.390
- Real quick.
Is this outfit cuter?

12:38.457 --> 12:41.460
- Leni, it's literally
the same outfit.

12:43.829 --> 12:46.065
Ah, where were we,
Boo-Boo Bear?

12:46.132 --> 12:47.666
Did you dream about
me last night?

12:47.733 --> 12:50.136
- Sure did, toots!
We were smooching.

12:50.202 --> 12:52.271
And you were loving it.
[kissing]

12:52.338 --> 12:54.507
- Ah! Luan!
- LUAN: [laughing]

12:54.573 --> 12:55.908
- Get out of here!

12:55.975 --> 12:57.576
[growling]

12:57.643 --> 12:59.111
- BOBBY: Babe,
what was that growl?

12:59.178 --> 13:01.347
Is there a gorilla
in there?

13:01.413 --> 13:03.249
- Guys, we have to talk.

13:03.315 --> 13:05.151
I am literally
almost an adult.

13:05.217 --> 13:06.752
I can't live like
this anymore.

13:06.819 --> 13:08.387
- So, you're finally
gonna see a doctor

13:08.454 --> 13:09.855
about your
flatulence problem?

13:09.922 --> 13:11.557
- What? I don't
have a flatulence problem!

13:11.624 --> 13:14.560
I'm talking about
living in this house.

13:14.627 --> 13:15.928
I can't even have
an uninterrupted

13:15.995 --> 13:17.897
conversation with Bobby
or sleep through the night

13:17.963 --> 13:19.431
without getting
kicked in the face.

13:19.498 --> 13:21.467
- Aren't you kind
of exaggerating?

13:23.169 --> 13:24.470
Oh.

13:24.537 --> 13:26.472
- So, I talked to Mom
and Dad and they said

13:26.539 --> 13:28.574
it was okay for me to
move into the garage.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.575
- OTHERS:
[gasping]

13:29.642 --> 13:32.845
- You can't leave!
We need you!

13:32.912 --> 13:33.879
- You'll be fine.

13:33.946 --> 13:35.447
Besides, I'll be
right by the house,

13:35.514 --> 13:37.049
if you need anything.

13:40.486 --> 13:43.789
- Oh, Lori, you're so lucky
you get your own room.

13:43.856 --> 13:46.525
- [toilet flushing]
- Bathroom's all set.

13:46.592 --> 13:49.028
Go easy on her at first.
No heavy meals.

13:49.094 --> 13:50.496
- Oh, I can't believe it.

13:50.563 --> 13:53.399
Our first little bird
is leaving the nest.

13:53.465 --> 13:55.801
- I said I wouldn't cry...
[sobbing]

13:55.868 --> 13:58.837
- You guys, I'm only
20 feet from the house,

13:58.904 --> 14:01.006
and you can visit
any time you want.

14:01.073 --> 14:02.441
But call, first.

14:02.508 --> 14:03.542
- [door slams]

14:03.609 --> 14:05.477
- Parents. Am I right?

14:05.544 --> 14:07.379
So, what are
we doing tonight?

14:07.446 --> 14:09.848
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- [door slams]

14:12.451 --> 14:13.986
- [long sigh]

14:14.053 --> 14:15.988
Alone at last.

14:16.055 --> 14:18.657
- [lively music]

14:18.724 --> 14:28.901
♪

14:28.968 --> 14:31.303
- [long sigh]
This is literally amazing.

14:31.370 --> 14:32.838
[yawning]
Well...

14:32.905 --> 14:34.974
[sighs]
...it must be about bedtime.

14:36.008 --> 14:37.710
- [clock beeps]

14:37.776 --> 14:38.911
- Hmmm...

14:38.978 --> 14:41.714
Hey, Boo-Boo Bear,
tell me about your day.

14:41.780 --> 14:43.716
- Sorry, babe, I'm really
slammed at the store.

14:43.782 --> 14:45.351
- CUSTOMERS:
[growling]

14:45.417 --> 14:47.052
- Well, fine.
I'm busy, too,

14:47.119 --> 14:48.754
so, 'bye.

14:53.192 --> 14:57.196
- Now gently rock forward
as we go into Crab Pose.

14:57.263 --> 14:58.197
- [grunting]

14:58.264 --> 14:59.732
[farts]
Ah!

14:59.798 --> 15:01.100
[groans]

15:01.166 --> 15:02.768
[eyes blink]

15:02.835 --> 15:04.403
[sighs]

15:04.470 --> 15:05.971
- [clock beeps]

15:07.906 --> 15:08.974
- Hi, Mr. Grouse.

15:09.041 --> 15:10.509
It looks like we're
going to be neighbors.

15:10.576 --> 15:12.211
- We're already neighbors.

15:12.278 --> 15:13.245
- Closer neighbors.

15:13.312 --> 15:14.613
I moved into the garage.

15:14.680 --> 15:16.148
- I don't care.

15:16.215 --> 15:18.150
- [lawnmower chugging]

15:20.185 --> 15:23.188
- Oh, I can't get this
tangle outta my hair!

15:23.255 --> 15:25.090
What am
I supposed to do?

15:25.157 --> 15:26.558
- Fear not, sibling.

15:26.625 --> 15:28.127
As it happens,
I've been working on

15:28.193 --> 15:29.662
a new detangling formula.

15:29.728 --> 15:31.130
- [liquid spritzes]
- [gasps]

15:32.931 --> 15:35.200
My hair!
What have you done?!

15:35.267 --> 15:38.337
- You should have specified
that you wanted to keep it.

15:38.404 --> 15:40.272
On a related note--
may I keep it?

15:40.339 --> 15:43.709
- This never would have
happened if Lori was here!

15:45.778 --> 15:47.579
- [squirrel squeaking]

15:47.646 --> 15:49.181
- [clock beeps]

15:49.248 --> 15:51.750
- Ah, finally, bedtime.

15:51.817 --> 15:54.920
- [lights click off]
- [animal howling]

15:54.987 --> 15:58.023
- It's darker out here
than I thought.

15:58.090 --> 16:00.259
- [branches scraping]
- [wind gusting]

16:00.326 --> 16:01.960
- [creaking noises]

16:04.797 --> 16:06.031
- [squirrel chattering]

16:06.098 --> 16:08.400
[chattering]
- [gasps]

16:08.467 --> 16:09.668
- [switch clicks]

16:09.735 --> 16:11.437
- [screaming]
- [switch clicking]

16:11.503 --> 16:13.906
- [teeth chattering]

16:13.972 --> 16:17.609
- Leni,
I had a nightmare.

16:17.676 --> 16:19.945
- It's okay.
Tell me about it.

16:20.012 --> 16:22.915
- Well, first, the blood-sucking
aliens were chasing me--

16:22.981 --> 16:24.883
- [gasps] Did they see
you come in here?

16:24.950 --> 16:26.885
Quick, help me
with this dresser!

16:26.952 --> 16:28.320
[straining]

16:28.387 --> 16:31.657
- I wish Lori was here.
She would make us feel safe.

16:31.724 --> 16:33.459
- I know,
but we can't bug her.

16:33.525 --> 16:34.860
She wants to be alone.

16:34.927 --> 16:40.899
- ♪

16:40.966 --> 16:42.835
- [musical ring tone]
- [gasps]

16:42.901 --> 16:43.736
Bobby!

16:43.802 --> 16:45.371
- Hey, babe.
How's Casa Lori?

16:45.437 --> 16:47.039
- Terrible.
This was a big mistake.

16:47.106 --> 16:48.307
- I'm sorry.

16:48.374 --> 16:50.209
Hey, why don't you just move
back in with the family?

16:50.275 --> 16:52.745
- I made such a big deal
about wanting to be on my own.

16:52.811 --> 16:54.246
If I came
crawling back now,

16:54.313 --> 16:55.614
they'd never let
me live it down.

16:55.681 --> 16:57.116
- Oops, babe,
I've gotta go.

16:57.182 --> 16:58.250
The exterminator's here.

16:58.317 --> 16:59.952
Papa thought he saw
a mouse in the store.

17:00.018 --> 17:01.620
It might have been
a moldy marshmallow,

17:01.687 --> 17:03.555
but we're not taking
any chances.

17:03.622 --> 17:06.724
- [bell dings]
- A mouse, huh? Hmmm...

17:08.394 --> 17:10.529
Okay, guys, scatter!

17:10.596 --> 17:12.030
- [mice squeaking]

17:12.097 --> 17:13.732
- Ahem!

17:13.799 --> 17:17.002
[screaming]
Help!

17:17.069 --> 17:18.036
- What's wrong?

17:18.103 --> 17:20.172
- There are literally
mice in here.

17:20.239 --> 17:21.740
- Oh, honey, I'm sure you're--
- [mice skittering]

17:21.807 --> 17:23.308
- DAD:
[screams]

17:23.375 --> 17:24.576
--moving back
into the house!

17:24.643 --> 17:26.912
This place is a horror show.
[sobbing]

17:26.979 --> 17:29.481
- Oh, and I love
it here so much.

17:29.548 --> 17:30.983
But if you say so.

17:32.384 --> 17:33.719
- I have a better
solution--

17:33.786 --> 17:36.155
my new ultrasonic
mousetrap.

17:38.123 --> 17:41.226
It works due to the simple-
minded nature of the mice.

17:41.293 --> 17:43.095
Not you, Leni.

17:43.162 --> 17:44.229
Problem solved.

17:44.296 --> 17:45.564
And it's a win-win.

17:45.631 --> 17:47.132
I get new research
subjects,

17:47.199 --> 17:49.902
and you get
your beloved abode back.

17:49.968 --> 17:51.170
- Great.

17:53.705 --> 17:55.574
Dad, the mice are gone.

17:55.641 --> 17:58.811
- Uh, yes, well...
glad I could help.

18:00.646 --> 18:02.681
- [wrench clanks]
- [water splashing]

18:04.016 --> 18:05.117
- Ahem.

18:05.184 --> 18:07.085
Help! I've got a leak!

18:08.353 --> 18:09.488
- [water splashing]

18:09.555 --> 18:11.356
- Unh-unh, this is bad.
You can't stay out here.

18:11.423 --> 18:12.591
- No!

18:12.658 --> 18:14.126
You're probably right.

18:14.193 --> 18:16.295
- Don't worry, sis.
I've got this.

18:16.361 --> 18:17.463
- [whistle shrills]

18:17.529 --> 18:18.964
- Bucket brigade!

18:19.031 --> 18:23.635
- ♪

18:23.702 --> 18:26.505
- I replaced the PVC
with galvanized steel,

18:26.572 --> 18:28.507
so she should
definitely hold now.

18:28.574 --> 18:30.509
- Great.

18:30.576 --> 18:32.845
- [door slams]
- You guys, help!

18:32.911 --> 18:35.147
I think the garage
is haunted.

18:35.214 --> 18:36.548
See?

18:36.615 --> 18:38.750
- "Get Out!"
Hmmm...

18:38.817 --> 18:39.852
- [lipstick tube rolls]

18:39.918 --> 18:41.587
- Let me do my thing.

18:41.653 --> 18:45.724
Oh, Spirit, speak to me.

18:45.791 --> 18:47.025
Hmmm...
[claps hands]

18:47.092 --> 18:48.727
The ghost just
explained everything.

18:48.794 --> 18:49.761
- There's really a ghost?

18:49.828 --> 18:51.797
I mean, of course,
there's a ghost,

18:51.864 --> 18:54.766
and, clearly,
he wants me to leave.

18:54.833 --> 18:57.436
- Actually, he said
you can stay.

18:57.503 --> 18:58.403
He's leaving.

18:58.470 --> 19:00.005
Something about
"yoga farts."

19:00.072 --> 19:02.608
- Okay, that was
the floorboards!

19:02.674 --> 19:04.209
- [door slams]

19:04.276 --> 19:05.410
- [sighs]

19:05.477 --> 19:07.346
There must be some
way out of here.

19:07.412 --> 19:08.914
- [lawnmower chugging]

19:09.815 --> 19:11.717
[lawnmower chugging]

19:11.783 --> 19:12.985
- [basketball thuds]

19:13.051 --> 19:15.454
- [gasps]

19:15.521 --> 19:16.855
- Dang it, Luna.

19:16.922 --> 19:18.891
Your fog machine warped
Mr. Coconut's head.

19:18.957 --> 19:20.726
- Can't prove it, dude!

19:20.792 --> 19:23.195
- Lincoln, tell her she has
to pay to get him fixed.

19:23.262 --> 19:24.696
- Um...okay.

19:24.763 --> 19:27.199
Luna, I think Luan
has a point.

19:27.266 --> 19:28.634
You should pay up.

19:28.700 --> 19:30.469
- You wanna think
again, brah?

19:30.536 --> 19:31.670
- Yes, I do.

19:31.737 --> 19:33.539
Luan, I think
you should accept

19:33.605 --> 19:35.440
that fog machines
are a part of life.

19:35.507 --> 19:37.509
- I wouldn't be
too hasty, Slick.

19:37.576 --> 19:39.611
My cousin's a baseball bat.

19:39.678 --> 19:41.146
- I wish Lori was here.

19:41.213 --> 19:43.515
She always has
the right solution.

19:43.582 --> 19:44.783
- That's your solution?

19:44.850 --> 19:47.886
That I drive my tractor
through your garage?

19:47.953 --> 19:52.024
- Yes, in exchange for
a tray of my dad's lasagna.

19:52.090 --> 19:53.625
- Well, what happens
when your old man

19:53.692 --> 19:55.661
wants me to pay
for the damage?

19:55.727 --> 19:57.729
- I'll give you the money
out of my allowance.

19:57.796 --> 20:01.300
- Hot dinner, and I get to
wreck your dad's garage?

20:01.366 --> 20:03.001
Now that's a win-win.

20:03.068 --> 20:05.404
- Let's say tonight
around 7:00.

20:08.974 --> 20:10.442
- Well, all done.

20:10.509 --> 20:12.277
I'd love to hang
out and "dish,"

20:12.344 --> 20:14.913
but I'm sure you wanna go
back to your place now.

20:14.980 --> 20:18.450
- Uh, first, I should
say goodnight to everyone.

20:18.517 --> 20:19.985
[zooming]

20:21.920 --> 20:24.056
Goodnight, Leni.
Goodnight, Luna.

20:24.122 --> 20:26.158
Goodnight, Lynn.
Goodnight, Lincoln.

20:26.224 --> 20:28.160
- Move, you're
blocking the TV.

20:28.226 --> 20:31.029
- Ah, well, now I'm gonna
have to start over.

20:31.096 --> 20:32.664
Goodnight, Leni.
Goodnight, Luna.

20:32.731 --> 20:34.132
Goodnight, Lynn.
- [lawnmower chugging]

20:34.199 --> 20:36.168
- [loud crash]
- LORI: [gasps]

20:36.234 --> 20:37.302
What was that?

20:37.369 --> 20:41.106
- Dang it! I put her
in reverse by mistake,

20:41.173 --> 20:43.609
and knocked down
the wrong garage.

20:43.675 --> 20:45.644
Can I still have
your dad's lasagna?

20:45.711 --> 20:47.679
- Knocked down
the wrong garage?

20:47.746 --> 20:49.214
- Dad's lasagna?

20:49.281 --> 20:52.818
- Lori, you've got
a "ricotta" explain' to do.

20:52.884 --> 20:55.153
[laughing]
Get it?

20:55.220 --> 20:56.521
- Heh. Heh.

20:56.588 --> 20:58.757
Well, I kind of maybe paid
Mr. Grouse to wreck the garage

20:58.824 --> 21:00.225
so I wouldn't have
to live there.

21:00.292 --> 21:02.327
- OTHERS: [shouting
mixed comments]

21:02.394 --> 21:03.996
- You love the garage.

21:04.062 --> 21:06.765
- I thought all I wanted was
to be away from you guys.

21:06.832 --> 21:08.967
But I only ended
up missing you.

21:09.034 --> 21:10.902
I was just too
embarrassed to admit it.

21:10.969 --> 21:14.473
- OTHERS: [shouting
mixed comments]

21:14.539 --> 21:16.642
- Nice reunion, Louds.

21:16.708 --> 21:18.210
But what about
my garage?

21:18.276 --> 21:20.379
- Here, I'll give
you a quote.

21:20.445 --> 21:22.214
- BOBBY: So, it turns
out it wasn't

21:22.280 --> 21:23.649
a moldy marshmallow
or a mouse.

21:23.715 --> 21:24.916
It was a chinchilla.

21:24.983 --> 21:26.051
I named it "Lori."

21:26.118 --> 21:28.553
- Oh, Boo-Boo Bear,
that's so sweet.

21:28.620 --> 21:30.188
Wait, is that
like a rat?

21:30.255 --> 21:32.457
- Lori,
what do you think?

21:32.524 --> 21:35.894
- Love. You literally
look like a model.

21:35.961 --> 21:38.130
- Lori, can I sleep
in your bed?

21:38.196 --> 21:40.932
- Of course.
Boots off.

21:42.167 --> 21:45.137
- Lori, tell Lisa she can't
harvest my kidneys.

21:45.203 --> 21:47.906
- Tell Lincoln
he only requires one.

21:47.973 --> 21:49.841
Now let's do this!

21:49.908 --> 21:51.910
- Lisa, you took
his appendix.

21:51.977 --> 21:53.078
Don't be greedy.

21:53.145 --> 21:54.880
- Yeah, Lisa,
have a "heart,"

21:54.946 --> 21:56.048
but just not mine.

21:56.114 --> 21:58.050
[laughing]
Get it?

21:58.116 --> 21:59.985
- Lori,
can you detangle?

22:00.052 --> 22:02.087
- You got it.
[sighs]

22:02.154 --> 22:04.256
I really missed
all of this.

22:04.322 --> 22:05.490
[screams]

22:11.763 --> 22:13.999
♪ May sound bad,
but ain't the case ♪

22:14.066 --> 22:16.968
♪ In the Loud House,
Loud House ♪

22:17.035 --> 22:19.705
♪ Duck and dodge
and push and shove ♪

22:19.771 --> 22:21.940
♪ That's the way
we show our love ♪

22:22.007 --> 22:24.776
♪ In the Loud House,
Loud House ♪

22:24.843 --> 22:26.078
♪ Laundry piles
stacked up high ♪

22:26.144 --> 22:27.512
♪ Hand-me-downs
that make me cry ♪

22:27.579 --> 22:29.247
♪ Stand in line
to take a pee ♪

22:29.314 --> 22:30.549
♪ Never any privacy ♪

22:30.615 --> 22:32.918
♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪

22:32.984 --> 22:35.387
♪ That's the way
it always is ♪

22:35.454 --> 22:36.688
♪ In the Loud House ♪♪
